The paper presents a methodology that uses deep learning methods to model coder decision making and that predicts ICD codes. This involves the use of machine learning algorithms and techniques, which are commonly associated with the computer science sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the use of clinical data and patient information, which could be associated with the sub-categories of cybernetics (cs.CY), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper involves the use of databases and data management techniques, which could be associated with the sub-category of databases (cs.DB).
